  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Can I pair the same wine with wild versus farmed salmon?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">While similar wines work for both, subtle adjustments improve the pairing. Wild salmon's leaner texture and more intense flavor pair beautifully with higher-acid wines like Chablis or Loire Valley Sauvignon Blanc. Farmed salmon's higher fat content can handle slightly richer wines such as lightly oaked Chardonnay or Pinot Grigio from Alto Adige. The key is matching the wine's weight to the salmon's richness level.</p>
